txt.en: 'I commend your efforts, [placeholder]! Come, let us return and report our success to the Free Peoples.'
'[placeholder], did you already take care of those scoundrels?!'
You should secure the Trestlespan.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>If Radhril is missing, and the Call Radhril skill is not available, try using the /pet release command.</rgb>
'Do not worry about the Trestlespan. I can defend it.'
You should secure the southern courtyard.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>If Radhril is missing, and the Call Radhril skill is not available, try using the /pet release command.</rgb>
'Quickly, head to the southern courtyard. It is still under attack!'
You should secure the southern gate.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>If Radhril is missing, and the Call Radhril skill is not available, try using the /pet release command.</rgb>
'The enemy has launched a counter attack!'
You have been tasked with investigating a fire in the Wildwood, then quickly returning to town.
Use the summoning horn west of Trestlebridge to summon Radhril to your side.
You should talk to Radhril.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>If Radhril is missing, and the Call Radhril skill is not available, try using the /pet release command.</rgb>
You should secure the western courtyard.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>If Radhril is missing, and the Call Radhril skill is not available, try using the /pet release command.</rgb>

'The fire was a ruse. It was merely a camp-fire, set ablaze by those unknown to us. I suspect someone wanted us to stray from town.\n\n'Look there! The Enemy attacks Trestlebridge! Quickly now, we must defeat the ambush and save the town!'
Use the Call Radhril skill and talk to Radhril
